![Distributed Web Infrastructure](images/diagramme3.png)


Additional Server

Improves capacity and reduces the load on individual servers.

Helps distribute tasks efficiently and prevents slowdowns.

Load Balancer (HAProxy) in Cluster

Distributes traffic across multiple servers to prevent overload and ensure availability.

Works in cluster mode with another load balancer for redundancy, avoiding a single point of failure.

Split Components

Web Server: Handles HTTP requests and serves pages to users.

Application Server: Processes business logic and user requests.

Database Server: Stores and manages website data, improving performance and security.